### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

`max` `maxLength` `min` `minLength` should only be present in the items of `todoForm` in the following code, not on the `todoForm` itself because it doesn't make any sense and the current api only allows to bind these rules on the items of the model only.  Currently, `form` function returns `FieldTree` type and it contains the following signature and I think these should be removed.

```typescript
readonly max?: Signal<number | undefined>;
readonly maxLength?: Signal<number | undefined>;
readonly min?: Signal<number | undefined>;
readonly minLength?: Signal<number | undefined>;
```


```typescript
todoModel = signal({
  title: '',
  description: '',
});

todoForm = form(this.todoModel, (model) => {
  apply(model.title, (field) => {
    required(field, { message: 'This field is required' });
    minLength(field, 3, { message: 'Enter minimum 3 characters' });
    maxLength(field, 50, { message: 'Enter max 50 characters' });
  });
});
```

